title: Grateful Dead Live at Boston Garden on 1994-09-27
lineage: Dat (Tascam DA-20) -> Tascam DA-3000 -> Samplitude Professional v11.2.1 -> FLAC/
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger, They Love Each Other, Minglewood Blues, So Many Roads, Maggie's Farm*-> Cumberland Blues Blues*, Easy Answers, Deal

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Women Are Smarter, Way to Go Home-> Corinna-> Uncle John's Band-> Drums-> Space-> All Along The Watchtower, Standing On the Moon,  E: Johnny B. Goode

reviews.review_text:
I am on an amazing journey I am listening to every 1994 show in order, mining for gold. 

Set 1 Highlights: Lightning Bolt is back, baby! Very good Stranger and TLEO to kick of this multi-night run at the Garden. Unfortunately, it sounds like Bobby went to Guitar Center and bought a $15 digital distortion pedal on the recommendation of a high school kid in a punk-ska-metal band. Pretty ironic that Dan Healy was dismissed for turning Bobby way down in the mixes, and when he is gone, this is what we get. 

Set 2 HIGHlights: China>Rider is quite nice. UJB jam is fairly interesting. SOTM features some excellent "be with you" moments. 

All in all, an okay show, but nothing great. Warming up.
